OL,3,C'Today I feel like me': Blind and
OL,4,Cdisabled people given chance to drive
OL,6,FHe said: "I first met Harvey when he
OL,7,Fwas 11, and he's just gone from
OL,8,Fstrength to strength. From being a
OL,9,Flittle bit intimidated by the cars, to
OL,10,Falmost driving them all by himself,
OL,11,Fand then taking that big leap onto the
OL,12,Froads and passing his driving test."
OL,14,FHarvey uses a specially adapted
OL,15,Fautomatic car, which uses an inner
OL,16,Fring inside of the steering wheel as
OL,17,Fthe accelerator and a side lever to
OL,18,Fbrake.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
