OL,3,C'Today I feel like me': Blind and
OL,4,Cdisabled people given chance to drive
OL,6,FHarvey is now able to drive
OL,7,Findependently, but is still getting
OL,8,Fused to the difference between public
OL,9,Froads and the race course.
OL,11,FHe said: "On the roads you've got
OL,12,Fspeed limits and you have to follow
OL,13,Fthe rules of the road. It is a very
OL,14,Fdifferent experience as on the track
OL,15,Fyou can go a lot faster, but they're
OL,16,Fboth equally as fun."
OL,18,F"I was told I'd never be able to
OL,19,Fdrive, I was told I'd never be able to
OL,20,Fdo a lot of things, but I've just gone
OL,21,Fahead and done it."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/10
